import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='x distribution')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    ax = name_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=name_counts.index.map(lambda x: data.loc[data['name'] == x, 'color'].iloc[0]))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of name?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Name")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend(name_counts.index, title="Names", loc="upper right")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
